{
  "texts": [
    "Rashwan et al. (2019) introduced a deep architecture called a matrix network for object detection.",
    "This architecture incorporates a scaling and aspect ratio sensing mechanism to enhance keypoint-based object detection.",
    "Recently, Ge et al. (2022a, b) proposed a GAN-based underwater image enhancement method to tackle the problem of underwater image degradation.",
    "They successfully created an underwater style dataset and made lightweight improvements to the model by combining the multiscale retinex with color restoration and Deha-zeNet (Cai et al. 2016), resulting in significant improvements in detection accuracy.",
    "Liu et al. (2022) redesigned an underwater enhancement method based on objectguided dual adversarial contrastive learning, and their approach achieved both visual friendliness and taskoriented enhancement."
  ]
}